title: Grateful Dead Live at Taft Auditorium on 1971-10-30
description:
Set 1

Bertha, Me & My Uncle, Sugaree, Beat It On Down The Line, Loser, Playin' In The Band, Tennessee Jed, Jack Straw, Big Railroad Blues, Me And Bobby McGee, Brown Eyed Women, One More Saturday Night

Set 2

Casey Jones, Mexicali Blues, Comes A Time, El Paso, Ramble On Rose, Sugar Magnolia, Truckin', Not Fade Away-> Goin' Down The Road Feelin' Bad-> Not Fade Away

FM broadcast - Other artist(s): NRPS

reviews.review_text: Jerry strong! Comes A Time...wow just incredible the emotion in his  voice IMHO Jerry just nails it baby!

I Was There Great show, crazy audience decked out for Halloween. The Dead had crates of one gallon jugs of Electric Kool-Aid on stage that they passed into the audience. Jerry played pedal steel for New Riders who opened, one of the last shows he played on stage with them. A truly memorable night.
Comes A Time My fav Comes A Time of all time.
